# MySQL Best Practices

## Database Design
- Use proper normalization (3NF minimum)
- Implement proper data types
- Use proper constraints (PK, FK, UNIQUE, CHECK)
- Design proper schema structure
- Use proper naming conventions
- Plan for scalability

## Table Structure
- Use BIGINT for primary keys (not INT)
- Implement proper column data types
- Use NOT NULL constraints where needed
- Set proper default values
- Add audit timestamps (created_at, updated_at)
- Document table purposes

## Naming Conventions
- Use snake_case for table and column names
- Use plural form for table names
- Prefix boolean columns with is/has/should
- Name foreign keys as parent_table_id format
- Use idx_ prefix for indexes
- Use uk_ prefix for unique constraints

## Constraints and Validation
- Use primary key on every table
- Implement foreign key constraints properly
- Use unique constraints for unique data
- Add check constraints for data validation
- Use NOT NULL for required fields
- Document all constraints

## Indexing Strategy
- Index all foreign keys
- Index frequently searched columns
- Create composite indexes for common queries
- Use proper index naming conventions
- Avoid over-indexing
- Monitor index performance

## Query Optimization
- Select specific columns (never SELECT *)
- Implement proper pagination with LIMIT
- Use proper JOIN syntax
- Avoid functions in WHERE clauses
- Implement proper subquery patterns
- Use EXPLAIN to analyze queries

## Data Types Selection
- Use DECIMAL for monetary values (not FLOAT)
- Use VARCHAR with proper length limits
- Use TEXT for large text content
- Use DATE for dates only
- Use TIMESTAMP for date and time
- Choose appropriate integer types

## Transaction Management
- Use transactions for related operations
- Implement proper isolation levels
- Use rollback for error handling
- Handle deadlocks properly
- Keep transactions short
- Document transaction flows

## Database Connections
- Implement connection pooling
- Use proper connection limits
- Handle connection timeouts
- Implement reconnection logic
- Monitor active connections
- Clean up connections properly

## Performance Optimization
- Analyze query execution plans
- Optimize slow queries
- Use proper caching strategies
- Implement database indexing
- Monitor query performance
- Avoid N+1 query problems

## Security
- Use parameterized queries (prevent SQL injection)
- Implement proper user permissions
- Use proper password hashing
- Encrypt sensitive data
- Validate all input data
- Implement access control

## Backup and Recovery
- Implement automated backups
- Test backup restoration
- Use proper backup retention
- Document recovery procedures
- Monitor backup success
- Implement disaster recovery plan

## Replication and Scaling
- Use proper replication setup
- Implement master-slave replication
- Monitor replication lag
- Handle replication failures
- Use proper read replicas
- Implement proper failover

## Monitoring and Logging
- Enable general query log for debugging
- Monitor slow query log
- Implement proper logging
- Monitor database performance
- Track resource usage
- Set up performance alerts

## Schema Changes
- Use proper migration management
- Test migrations in development
- Implement zero-downtime migrations
- Document all schema changes
- Use proper versioning
- Plan for rollbacks

## Data Integrity
- Use foreign key constraints
- Validate data constraints
- Implement proper checksums
- Monitor data consistency
- Handle orphaned records
- Maintain referential integrity

